VALUES ('f0d7cd19-4042-453a-bbbb-987a549a1819', 'The author of Text 2 would most likely criticize Text 1 for which of the following?', 'Text 1
In 2012, economist Tomas Vela argued that automation would uniformly eliminate manufacturing jobs within a decade, citing early robotics deployments at automotive plants. His forecast treated every factory task as equally machine-replaceable and predicted retraining could absorb displaced workers only if launched immediately at national scale. Longitudinal plant data had not yet accumulated when editorial boards amplified the claim. The authors caution that replication remains necessary before treating the finding as settled. The authors caution that replication remains necessary before treating the finding as settled. Follow-up work will test whether

Text 2
A 2020 comparative study argued analytic languages express grammatical relationships through word order and particles rather than through inferior instruction methods. Swahili attaches verb prefixes for agreement while Mandarin relies on fixed Subject-Verb-Object structures. The study recommends teaching both systems by contrasting operational mechanisms instead of ranking language families hierarchically. The authors caution that replication remains necessary before treating the finding as settled. The authors caution that replication remains necessary before treating the finding as settled. Follow-up work will test whether the pattern holds across additional sites and populations.', 'passage', '[{"id":"A","text":"By claiming Text 2 abandons the shared topic entirely, treating a methodological dispute as proof the texts address unrelated disciplines in context.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"[Mutual Consensus Decoy] [Scope Creep] Attributes an extreme generalized position beyond either text''s guarded assertions."},{"id":"B","text":"By comparing the texts'' citation counts, an external metric neither author uses to evaluate the validity of the competing claims as written.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"[Scope Creep] [Out-of-Bound Contrast] Contrasts the texts on a variable neither author discusses."},{"id":"C","text":"By broadening Text 1''s theoretical frame because Text 2 links outcomes to conditions Text 1''s model omits yet does not deny entirely.","is_correct":true,"explanation":"Correct (C). Correct (C). This choice captures how Text 2 responds to Text 1''s claim without overstating agreement or inventing variables neither text mentions."},{"id":"D","text":"By conceding that Text 1''s strawman accurately represents all opposing views, though Text 2 supplies alternative mechanisms Text 1 overlooks throughout","is_correct":false,"explanation":"[Out-of-Bound Contrast] [Mutual Consensus Decoy] Claims Text 2 agrees with a claim Text 2 actually rejects or qualifies."}]'::jsonb, 'C', 'Step 1 — Summarize each text
Focus on {{yellow:treating}} in the passage. The cross text response item asks you to summarize each text before comparing choices.

Step 2 — Compare the perspectives
Compare each option against explicit textual evidence. On hard items, correct answers usually restate the passage faithfully without absolute words the text does not support.

Step 3 — Choose the best response
Choice C is correct: By broadening Text 1''s theoretical frame because Text 2 links outcomes to conditions Text 1''s model omits yet does not deny entirely..

Distractor analysis:
- A: [Mutual Consensus Decoy] [Scope Creep] Attributes an extreme generalized position beyond either text''s guarded assertions.
- B: [Scope Creep] [Out-of-Bound Contrast] Contrasts the texts on a variable neither author discusses.
- D: [Out-of-Bound Contrast] [Mutual Consensus Decoy] Claims Text 2 agrees with a claim Text 2 actually rejects or qualifies.', NULL, 'Craft and Structure', 'Cross-Text Connections', 'reading_writing', 'craft', 'CTC', NULL, 'hard', false, 'SAT', 'multiple_choice', true, true, 'scholaris_ai', '{"dsat_blueprint_v1":true,"rw_subtype":"cross_text_response","rw_format":"text_1_text_2","generator":"regenerate-english-fresh.mjs","regen_seed_offset":100000,"explanation_v2":true}'::jsonb, now(), now());
